'''Photo London''' is an annual photography event held at [[Somerset House]] in London in May.<ref name="sh-pl">"[https://www.somersethouse.org.uk/whats-on/photo-london Photo London]". [[Somerset House]]. Accessed 9 February 2018.</ref><ref name="guardian-brown">{{cite news | url = https://www.theguardian.com/artanddesign/2014/nov/06/photo-london-to-transform-photography-audience-somerset-house-fair | date = 6 November 2014 | accessdate = 9 February 2018 | first = Mark | last = Brown | newspaper = [[The Guardian]] | location = London | title = Photo London ‘to utterly transform the photography audience’}}</ref> Galleries<ref name="telegraph-gleadell">{{cite news | url = https://www.telegraph.co.uk/luxury/art/can-photo-london-attract-worlds-photography-collectors-capital/ | date = 16 May 2017 | accessdate = 9 February 2018 | first = Colin | last = Gleadell | newspaper = [[The Daily Telegraph]] | location = London | title = Can Photo London attract the world’s photography collectors to the capital?}}</ref> and publishers show and sell work by photographers, and there are curated exhibitions and talks.<ref name="ft-2017">{{cite news | url = https://www.ft.com/photolondon2017 | date = 11 May 2017 | accessdate = 9 February 2018 | first = | last = | newspaper = [[Financial Times]] | location = London | title = Photo London 2017}}</ref> Awards are also given.<ref name="ft-2017" />
It was established in 2004 and ran until 2006 at the [[Royal Academy of Arts]], then at [[Old Billingsgate Market|Old Billingsgate]] in 2007, then stopped.<ref name="fad">Mark Westall, "[https://fadmagazine.com/2007/04/04/photo-london/ photo-london]". FAD, 4 April 2007. Accessed 9 February 2018.</ref> It was relaunched in 2015 and has since been held at Somerset House.<ref name="sh-pl" />
==Details== Photo London was established in 2004 by Daniel Newburg and held at the [[Royal Academy of Arts]] in 2004, 2005 and 2006.<ref name="fad" /><ref name="antiquestradegazette">"[https://www.antiquestradegazette.com/news/2007/photo-london-new-owners-new-venue-new-content/ Photo-London: new owners, new venue, new content]". [[Antiques Trade Gazette]], 19 March 2007. 9 February 2018</ref><ref name="independent-cripps">{{cite news | url = https://www.independent.co.uk/arts-entertainment/photography/london-is-back-in-the-frame-with-its-first-international-photography-fair-in-eight-years-10264864.html | date = 22 May 2015 | accessdate = 9 February 2018 | first = Charlotte | last = Cripps | newspaper = [[The Independent]] | location = London | title = London is back in the frame with its first international photography fair in eight years}}</ref> In November 2006 it was purchased by [[Reed Exhibitions]] (who also owned [[Paris Photo]]).<ref name="fad" /><ref name="antiquestradegazette" /><ref name="independent-cripps" /> Reed ran it, with Newburg acting as creative director, in 2007 at [[Old Billingsgate Market|Old Billingsgate]] and then stopped.<ref name="fad" /><ref name="antiquestradegazette" /><ref name="independent-cripps" /> Photo London was re-launched in 2015 by a company Candlestar, led by Michael Benson and Fariba Farshad.<ref name="sh-pl" /><ref name="independent-cripps" /><ref>"[https://photolondon.org/about/directors/ Directors]". Photo London. Accessed 9 February 2018.</ref><ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.amateurphotographer.co.uk/latest/articles/photo-london-2016-key-highlights-75089 | date = 4 May 2016 | accessdate = 9 February 2018 | first = Karen | last = Sheard | publisher = [[Amateur Photographer]] | title = Photo London 2016 – our must-see highlights of this year’s fair}}</ref>
At Photo London, galleries<ref name="telegraph-gleadell" /> and publishers show and sell work by photographers, and there are curated exhibitions and talks.<ref name="ft-2017" />
Other photography events held at the same time in London include the [[Prix Pictet]] exhibition at the [[Victoria and Albert Museum]], the [[Deutsche Börse Photography Prize]] exhibition at [[The Photographers' Gallery]], the Peckham 24 photography festival in south-east London, and Offprint, an independent photobook publishers' fair at [[Tate Modern]].<ref name="ft-2017" /><ref>{{cite news | url = https://www.standard.co.uk/go/london/arts/photo-london-fair-features-model-turns-from-kate-moss-and-christy-turlington-a3541251.html | date = 17 May 2017 | accessdate = 9 February 2018 | first = Benedict | last = Moore-Bridger | newspaper = [[London Evening Standard]] | location = London | title = Photo London fair features model turns from Kate Moss and Christy Turlington}}</ref>
