ent|language=Dutch|accessdate=16 April 2009}}</ref> *1927: [[Jeanne Louise Milde]], sculpture<ref>[http://enciclopedia.itaucultural.org.br/pessoa239899/jeanne-louise-milde Jeanne Louise Milde]. Enciclopédia Itaú Cultural. {{pt}}</ref> *1932: [[Jean Boedts]], engraving<ref name=Egypt/> *1932: [[Willy Kreitz]], sculpture<ref name=Egypt/> *1933: [[Jozef-Louis Stynen]], architecture<ref>{{cite book|last1=De Maeyer|first1=Jan|title=Negentiende-eeuwse restauratiepraktijk en actuele monumentenzorg|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=j88k1JFXLc0C&pg=PA249&dq=%22prijs+van+rome%22&lr=&as_brr=3&ei=dqrlSbOmGYjCMonP7ZcN#PPA250,M1|accessdate=15 April 2009|year=1999|publisher=Leuven University Press|language=Dutch|isbn=|page=250}}</ref> *1933: [[Prosper Van Eechaute]], music<ref>{{cite web|title=Maart 06 agenda|url=http://www.kcb.be/pages_agenda_nl/2005-2006/maa06.pdf|publisher=Koninklijk Conservatorium van Brussel|language=Dutch|accessdate=15 April 2009}}</ref> *1935: [[Alphonse Darville]], sculpture<ref>{{cite web|title=Alphonse Darville|url=http://charleroi-museum.org/mba/code/fr/expo_darville.htm |publisher=Musée des Beaux-Arts|location=Charleroi|language=French|accessdate=17 April 2009}}</ref> * 1935 - Cantata ''Le Vieux Soudard'', Léon Simar (1909-1983) second prize (music) *1936: [[Victor Blommaert]], architecture<ref name=Baeckelmans>{{cite book|last1=Bergmans|first1=Anna|title=Neostijlen in de negentiende eeuw |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=wkWPUw0VvUcC&pg=PA249&dq=%22prijs+van+rome%22&lr=&as_brr=3&ei=dqrlSbOmGYjCMonP7ZcN|accessdate=15 April 2009|year=2002 |publisher=Leuven University Press|language=Dutch|isbn=978-90-5867-262-9|page=249}}</ref> *1937: [[Jan Cobbaert]], painting<ref>{{cite web|title=Biografie|url=http://www.cobbaertjan.be/biografie.html|publisher=Jan Cobbaert|language=Dutch|accessdate=15 April 2009}}</ref> * 1937 - Cantata ''Le Trapèze Étoilé'', Léon Simar (1909-1983) first prize (music) *1939: [[Leo De Budt]], painting {{citation needed|date=Mar