{{italic title}}
'''''Torquemada''''' is an 1869 [[Play (theatre)|play]] by [[Victor Hugo]] about [[Tomás de Torquemada]] and the [[Inquisition]] in Spain. It criticized [[religious fanaticism]] and fanatical [[catholic]]ism. It was first published in 1882, as a protest against [[antisemitic]] [[pogrom]]s in Russia at the time.<ref>{{cite book |author=John Andrew Frey |year=1999 |title=A Victor Hugo encyclopedia |edition=2nd |publisher=Greenwood Publishing Group |page=264 |isbn=9780313298967 }}</ref>

